<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 1:50AM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of north central
Randall and southeastern Potter Counties through 215 AM CDT...
At 149 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles west of Amarillo, moving northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Amarillo.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
